Video Frame Sampling Strategies Comparison. Three panels: 1) FRAME STACKING: All frames at once -> Good for short clips (<30s), Expensive (30 frames * tokens). 2) HIERARCHICAL SUMMARIZATION: Groups of 5 frames -> Segment Summaries -> Final Summary -> Good for long videos. 3) KEYFRAME DETECTION: Scene Change Detection -> Only Significant Frames -> Optimal for variable content. Cost/Quality tradeoff annotations. German labels.